        </div>
        <div class="beginner-note-content">
            <h4>Think of Controllers Like Restaurant Managers</h4>
            <p><strong>Controllers = The decision-makers that handle user requests</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Simple analogy:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>User Request</strong> = Customer ordering food</li>
                <li><strong>Controller</strong> = Restaurant manager who takes the order</li>
                <li><strong>Action Method</strong> = Specific task (take order, serve food, handle complaints)</li>
                <li><strong>Response</strong> = Food served to customer</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>In web terms:</strong> Controllers decide what happens when users visit different pages!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="important-note">
        <h4><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Important Setup Note</h4>
        <p>When creating this project in Visual Studio 2022, make sure to select <strong>ASP.NET Core Web App (Model-View-Controller)</strong>, NOT Console App!</p>
