    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
        <p>Now that you understand .NET basics, let's dive into the heart of web applications: <strong>Controllers</strong>. In ASP.NET Core, controllers are classes that handle web requests and return responses. They're like the "brain" of your web application!</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Remember:</strong> Every time you click a link or submit a form on a website, a controller somewhere is handling that request and deciding what to show you next.
