                        <li><code>[HttpGet]</code> - Used for pages that display information (default, can be omitted)</li>
                        <li><code>[HttpPost]</code> - Used for handling form submissions</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Why two About methods?</strong> One shows the form (GET), the other processes it (POST). Same URL, different HTTP methods.</p>
                    <p><strong>Parameters:</strong> Values from the URL (like "John") automatically get passed to the method.</p>
                </div>
