    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Controllers</strong> are classes that handle web requests and return responses</li>
            <li>When creating project: Select <strong>ASP.NET Core Web App (MVC)</strong> in Visual Studio 2022</li>
            <li>Controller names <strong>must end with "Controller"</strong> (e.g., HomeController)</li>
            <li><strong>[HttpGet]</strong> shows pages, <strong>[HttpPost]</strong> handles form submissions</li>
            <li><strong>Action methods</strong> are public methods that handle specific URLs</li>
            <li>The <strong>Index()</strong> method is the default action for a controller</li>
            <li><strong>View()</strong> returns HTML pages, <strong>Json()</strong> returns API data</li>
            <li><strong>URL routing</strong> follows pattern: /Controller/Action/Parameters</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

